    {
      "id": "3531ad49c5876bebefad0e9d9c4161b47d314246",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-07-31 15:05:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nSo why go to this complicated approach instead of adding a refcount to the set for every request in flight (and conversely substracting one for every completion)?\n\nYou approach is also potentially racy in a way that if there are no more refocunts held outside of the one you are releasing then the race would cause the racing request to access freed set.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "7f44b952b3cb4200042804465d082e8dd37c1cab",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 103,
        "name": "Zhenyu Xu",
        "email": "bobijam@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bobijam"
      },
      "date": "2012-08-01 02:54:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> So why go to this complicated approach instead of adding a refcount to the set for every request in flight (and conversely substracting one for every completion)?\n\nEven we use refcount approach, we still need make sure that the lov_finished_set() check in the cb_xxx_update() returns 1 for the last updated request, since cb_xxx_update() for each request is asynchronous callback.\n\nThat's what idempotent parameter of lov_finished_set() and lov_request_set::set_finish_checked for. When lov_finished_set() is used in cb_xxx_update(), it meant to return true for the last updated request, we use non-idempotent check. \n\n> You approach is also potentially racy in a way that if there are no more refocunts held outside of the one you are releasing then the race would cause the racing request to access freed set.\n\nif cb_xxx_update() are not run for every request, the set's refcount will not be released, that's the design purpose of lov_request_set.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "cef7b6a206c47ea915b35f875baff81aaa7c03b7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2012-08-02 22:52:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, approved\n\nok, I guess we can land it as is.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
